The paper discusses a model of social polling, which involves voting and influence among agents in a social network. This topic is closely related to social computing (cs.SI), game theory (cs.GT), and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also touches on the computational complexity of the problem, which is a common theme in theoretical computer science (cs.THE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the network structure, which is a key aspect of social networks (cs.SOC).
